{"name":"AC to DC Conversion","formula_count":0,"columns":[],"rows":[{"index":2,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B2","row":2,"column":2,"value":"STEP ONE","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":3,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B3","row":3,"column":2,"value":"Tum the gas off and prop the Banshee up to make access easier. Remove the Footpeg, shifter and stator cover from the left side of the engine. Also, remove the front plastic, tank and seat to access the stator wiring.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":5,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B5","row":5,"column":2,"value":"STEP TWO","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":6,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B6","row":6,"column":2,"value":"You will need a puller to remove the flywheeL Remove it and set it somewhere safe.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":8,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B8","row":8,"column":2,"value":"STEP THREE","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":9,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B9","row":9,"column":2,"value":"Locate the stator and mark its position, as this is important during reassembly. Locate the stator ground wire (shown), and carefully remove the epoxy around the connection.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":11,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B11","row":11,"column":2,"value":"STEP FOUR","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":12,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B12","row":12,"column":2,"value":"Hook up the soldered joint and remove the ground wire from the ground lug. Straighten out the connection and solder a new piece of wire (approximately 3 feet long) to the end of the wire. Add a small piece of shrink tubing to the joint to seal it.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":14,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B14","row":14,"column":2,"value":"STEP FIVE","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":15,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B15","row":15,"column":2,"value":"Route the new wire around the stator poles and group with the other wires and pull the loose end of the wire to the end of the loom where it meets the connector.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":17,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B17","row":17,"column":2,"value":"STEP SIX","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":18,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B18","row":18,"column":2,"value":"After reinstalling the Stator you can use Trail Tech's regulator/rectifier/battery kit and the new floating ground to tie into the new electronics per the instructors. Doing so will convert the Banshee's electrical supply from AC (alternating current) to DC (direct current). DC current is required to run high-output LED and HID lighting.","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":20,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B20","row":20,"column":2,"value":"STEP SEVEN","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":true,"size":11.0}}]},{"index":21,"hidden":false,"cells":[{"coordinate":"B21","row":21,"column":2,"value":"Install the lighting of your choice!","formula":null,"cached":null,"locked":true,"font":{"bold":false,"size":11.0}}]}],"images":[{"asset":"workbook_media_54.png","sha256":"21d19d8e1ef19010ab851c4fc5f3ef6acbea55116c64260dfeb8a740b2f1b5bc","width":960,"height":1023,"format":"png","anchor":{"row":2,"column":4},"order":1},{"asset":"workbook_media_55.png","sha256":"b9bf7c92327661e74410e73982fec1fa9588ba6aceb50e4a6b450373dd88f7cf","width":751,"height":1023,"format":"png","anchor":{"row":2,"column":20},"order":2},{"asset":"workbook_media_57.png","sha256":"942af323ff275fdfa81b7b08e95b9c29e55c300115b5702e850db4cbf3aa01f8","width":960,"height":1242,"format":"png","anchor":{"row":32,"column":4},"order":3},{"asset":"workbook_media_58.png","sha256":"047608808f31fa2ae98a63b5ee604b8ac1e22b2807b7b0ce7c765f537350e1be","width":960,"height":1242,"format":"png","anchor":{"row":32,"column":20},"order":4}]}
